Merge pull request #1520 from sharetribe/cms-page

PageBuilder for page assets retrieved from Asset Delivery API (created in Console)
CTA button in blocks: remove custom styling
Page: publisher seemed to confuse Google's structured data
PageBuilder: extract field data inside 'meta' object of page asset
Field: handle field types in 'meta' data
util/seo.js: OpenGraph and Twitter should use socialSharingTitle and socialSharingDescription
util/data.js: omit exposed image resolver configs

Prepare CMSPage, LandingPage, PrivacyPage, TermsOfServicePage for 'meta'
All the 'meta' data comes from page asset file and it's handled inside PageBuilder.
Change in page asset schema: ingress -> description

Omit invalid props warning from field types: headings, paragraph, markdown
Removing content input results as empty string in the saved asset.
Field type customAppearance: rename color as backgroundColor
Field: rename background key as appearance
Field types: customBackground and defaultBackground are renamed as customAppearance and defaultAppearance
Links (internalButtonLink and externalButtonLink) use content instead of label due to consistency
Rename fieldKey.type as fieldKey.fieldType (fieldType is as specific concept as sectionType and blockType)
BlockBuilder: remove complex not empty rules
BlockDefault: don't render internal parts of a block if there's no data
SectionBuilder: remove complex not empty rules
fix padding issues for the first block and sync carousel-column horizontal whitespace
PageBuilder: update Link component to support anchors.
CMSPage: allow pageId to be passed through extraProps in routeConfiguration
Remove margin-top from inline elements (a and code)
SectionCarousel: use any-hover media query instead of hover
Field: remove the warning of different forms of empty fields that might get passed through asset file
Field: 'label' for link is optional and so is 'alt' for image
Field: add propType shape for 'youtube' field
SectionContainer: add custom background only if type is correct
Field.helpers.js: refactor and improve link and image exposers
SectionBuilder: fix warning, when sectionId is not unique (operator error)
SectionCarousel: fix error, when no blocks are given
Lazy load Youtube iframe to improve page performance if iframe is below the fold.
SectionCarousel: no need to show arrows for touch devices
Changes by Vesa: SectionBuilder should not warn about custom sections
Changes by Vesa: customBackground should handle bg color
Changes by Vesa: add image field only if background is given
Changes by Vesa: handle title attribute of Link components
Changes by Vesa: use customBackground type in examples
Changes by Vesa: add CSS comments and avoid useless calc()

add dark theme support, disable rendering empty divs and vertical spacing between elements (Janne's commit splitted)
feedback reactions and fixes

Edit LandingPage/Fallback (Janne's commit splitted)
changes to LandingPage FallBack
TermsOfServicePage is built with PageBuilder and Asset Delivery API. It defaults to fallback page
Add initial version of Youtube video support
Remove hexColor field in favor of 'customBackground'
Check possible isDarkTheme through background key instead of top-level textColor
Change sections to work with updated SectionContainer
Add CustomBackground to Field.js and add prop validator
Add CustomBackground Primitive component (uses ResponsiveImage though)
Fix: don't include empty header container

Add PreviewResolverPage for Console preview links.
E.g. '/preview?asset-path=content/pages/about.json'
Remove hard-coded AboutPage in favor of CMSPage and about page asset
PrivacyPolicyPage is built with PageBuilder and Asset Delivery API. It defaults to fallback page
TermsOfServicePage is built with PageBuilder and Asset Delivery API. It defaults to fallback page

SectionBuilder: add isInsideContainer prop
for cases where sections are shown inside a wrapper (like Modal).

Update LandingPage container to start using PageBuilder
Include initial version of fallback page/asset
app.test: update to work with new LandingPage setup
Add util function to denormalize asset data

Fix a race that could lead to orders out of sync in user data

The issue was in possibility to receive connect right after sending
new order request, thus new order won't be in pending_orders and
handler may complete fetching without it, while its executionReport
was missed during disconnect. While this event is extremely unlikely
it was still possible. The solution is to protect adding the pending
order with mutex that is acquired right before sending new order and
released right after adding order to the set of pending ones.

Updates various dependencies to support React 18. Also updates to latest version of react-intersection-observer.

Feature: Debounced/delayed Loading (#11)

* Add utils and delayed loading test in stories

* Intermediate solution

Not sure where the reducer/update function is headed, but we'll
find out, I suppose.

* Finish refactoring

* Make buffering work

It works, but now the intersection logic is not the same. Scrolling
until inView is true, and then up, triggers the promise cancelation.
This is undesirable. We want the image to keep loading as long as
it stays on the screen. Oddly, scrolling past the image, and it
being in view, still lets it load without canceling (as intendeed).
Another difference is that loading only commences once the image is
fully in view, rather than on the margin.

* Document things a bit better

* There was no bug; the placeholder had a 0 height!

* A few more docs

* Name things, expose as props

Added:
- debugActions: logs actions in dev, warns and logs in prod
- debounceDurationMs: whether, and how much to debounce loading,
  0 by default, so no change to v1. Added codepath to make it so.
- Provisional changes.md document with API compatibility
- Various TODOs and cleanup tasks

* Fix passing of debounceDurationMs to cb

* Use debugActions in the story, destructure it

Also add a note to hopefully remember to destructure next time :)

* Pin microbundle and ts versions

* Clean dir before build

* TS BUG: need declaration: false to build correctly

If we set declaration: true, then typescript (specifically rpt2,
Rollup's TS plugin) fails with a cryptic path error. This is
filed under https://github.com/Microsoft/TypeScript/issues/25047.

Curiously, this does not happen on master, and I have vaguely
traced it back to unionize and the fact that it does fancy type
exports, which we partially re-export here. We would have to
manually emit a declaration file, which is not hard tbh, but a bit
annoying. Even funnier, webpack has no issue building in storybook,
but that might be because it does not emit declarations anyway.

Steps:
- Get declaration file from master, add to repository, and copy to
dist/ upon build;
- See if massaging our exports fixes it;
- Wait for TS :/

* 1.1.0-rc.1

* Version bump

* Make update static, use Commands

The Elm/JS/Redux/React-Component fusion is complete. The reducer
is now a pure function, because it only describes side-effects,
and does not execute them. The logic is really nice to read there.

* Naming things

* Version bump

* Use TS3.0

* Copy definitions separately

Because of the "path undefined" bug, we have to run `tsc`
separately, to get the definitions and copy them over.

* Do not expose Buffering as a separate state

Expose it under 'Loading' for backwards compatibility

* Improve debounceDurationMs docs

* Add first point to README

* Cancel Promises, clear cache on unmount

* Add docs for debounceDurationMs

Use files under src/ directly

Ambivalent about this, as I like testing the bundled output

Add real image with alt text to stories

Split logic into LazyImageFull

LazyImageFull allows for more fine-grained rendering based on
the state. This is particularly useful for css transitions and
when re-rendering is undesirable. LazyImage has been reimplemented
on top of this.

refactor: Remove cls render prop argument

BREAKING CHANGE
The cls property was not adding much, since we are not using it
as a hook for styling in the library. There is an argument that
we could use it for fallbacks, but that requires the user to
set the style tag anyway. Thus, it is best to leave it undefined.
It also bloated the syntax quite a bit, with a mess of squgglies
that can easily be messed up; JSX prop, arrow function, and then
destructuring. {({cls}) => ... }. I think this is more convenient
for people to use, especially weighed against the lack of benefit
to the library.

Long train of thoughts about this, but the solutions to noscript
working in React are either unsafe or cumbersome. Neither of those
should be imposed on the users unwttingly, so I thought it best
to leave notes but remove the fallback prop.

It breaks coding style
Fix a race that could lead to orders out of sync in user data

The issue was in possibility to receive connect right after sending
new order request, thus new order won't be in pending_orders and
handler may complete fetching without it, while its executionReport
was missed during disconnect. While this event is extremely unlikely
it was still possible. The solution is to protect adding the pending
order with mutex that is acquired right before sending new order and
released right after adding order to the set of pending ones.
Fix print in multiple_coins_strategy.py

Scouting message had a possibility for None-type exception
Fix the data race on cache.balances R/W

Bunch of data races were possible (one confirmed to happen) due to lack
of any shared access syncing
Fix out of sync issue for !userData stream

The problem was in missing server pushes during websocket reconnect.
The fix is to fetch with REST API any pending orders on connect event.
Workaround for apprise tag detection

Our coins representation became an open html tag by the
recent apprise version's opinion. We should retreat.

Switch websockets backend to ubwa

Mostly straightforward, we use UnicornFy to deal with full names in

resembles what j-waters previously done.

And there is a crucial fix in logger.py due to ubwa using root logger

1.1.0
Feature: Debounced/delayed Loading (#11)

* Add utils and delayed loading test in stories

* Intermediate solution

Not sure where the reducer/update function is headed, but we'll
find out, I suppose.

* Finish refactoring

* Make buffering work

It works, but now the intersection logic is not the same. Scrolling
until inView is true, and then up, triggers the promise cancelation.
This is undesirable. We want the image to keep loading as long as
it stays on the screen. Oddly, scrolling past the image, and it
being in view, still lets it load without canceling (as intendeed).
Another difference is that loading only commences once the image is
fully in view, rather than on the margin.

* Document things a bit better

* There was no bug; the placeholder had a 0 height!

* A few more docs

* Name things, expose as props

Added:
- debugActions: logs actions in dev, warns and logs in prod
- debounceDurationMs: whether, and how much to debounce loading,
  0 by default, so no change to v1. Added codepath to make it so.
- Provisional changes.md document with API compatibility
- Various TODOs and cleanup tasks

* Fix passing of debounceDurationMs to cb

* Use debugActions in the story, destructure it

Also add a note to hopefully remember to destructure next time :)

* Pin microbundle and ts versions

* Clean dir before build

* TS BUG: need declaration: false to build correctly

If we set declaration: true, then typescript (specifically rpt2,
Rollup's TS plugin) fails with a cryptic path error. This is
filed under https://github.com/Microsoft/TypeScript/issues/25047.

Curiously, this does not happen on master, and I have vaguely
traced it back to unionize and the fact that it does fancy type
exports, which we partially re-export here. We would have to
manually emit a declaration file, which is not hard tbh, but a bit
annoying. Even funnier, webpack has no issue building in storybook,
but that might be because it does not emit declarations anyway.

Steps:
- Get declaration file from master, add to repository, and copy to
dist/ upon build;
- See if massaging our exports fixes it;
- Wait for TS :/

* 1.1.0-rc.1

* Version bump

* Make update static, use Commands

The Elm/JS/Redux/React-Component fusion is complete. The reducer
is now a pure function, because it only describes side-effects,
and does not execute them. The logic is really nice to read there.

* Naming things

* Version bump

* Use TS3.0

* Copy definitions separately

Because of the "path undefined" bug, we have to run `tsc`
separately, to get the definitions and copy them over.

* Do not expose Buffering as a separate state

Expose it under 'Loading' for backwards compatibility

* Improve debounceDurationMs docs

* Add first point to README

* Cancel Promises, clear cache on unmount

* Add docs for debounceDurationMs

0.7.0
refactor: Remove cls render prop argument

BREAKING CHANGE
The cls property was not adding much, since we are not using it
as a hook for styling in the library. There is an argument that
we could use it for fallbacks, but that requires the user to
set the style tag anyway. Thus, it is best to leave it undefined.
It also bloated the syntax quite a bit, with a mess of squgglies
that can easily be messed up; JSX prop, arrow function, and then
destructuring. {({cls}) => ... }. I think this is more convenient
for people to use, especially weighed against the lack of benefit
to the library.
